Note:
Runa Standard Library: Advanced Text Parsing and Grammar Framework

Production-grade parsing system designed to surpass competitors like ANTLR,
PEG.js, Nearley, Tree-sitter, and language-specific parser generators.
Comprehensive parsing with advanced grammar analysis and error recovery.

Key Features:
- Complete parser generator with multiple parsing strategies
- Advanced grammar analysis with conflict detection and resolution
- Left recursion elimination and grammar transformation
- Sophisticated error recovery and diagnostic reporting
- AST construction with visitor pattern support
- Incremental parsing for real-time editing scenarios
- Multi-language grammar support with Unicode awareness
- Performance-optimized parsing with memoization
- Grammar debugging and profiling tools
- Semantic actions and attribute grammars
- Parser combination and modular grammar composition
- Advanced tokenization with context-sensitive lexing
- Parse tree visualization and analysis tools
- Grammar inference from examples
- Fuzzing and property-based testing integration

Architecture:
Built on Runa's natural language primitives with optimized parsing
algorithms and comprehensive grammar analysis. Provides both high-level
parser generators and low-level parsing primitives for maximum
flexibility and performance in text processing applications.
:End Note

Import "../../collections" as Collections
Import "string/format" as Format
Import "text/unicode" as Unicode

Note: Core Parsing Types and Structures
Type called "Grammar":
