Process called "generate_error_suggestions" that takes token as Token returns List[String]:
    Note: Generate helpful suggestions for parse errors
    Let suggestions be list containing Match token.type:
    When "IDENTIFIER":
            Add "Check if identifier is spelled correctly" to suggestions
            Add "Verify identifier is declared before use" to suggestions
    When "NUMBER":
            Add "Check number format" to suggestions
    When "STRING":
            Add "Check string delimiters" to suggestions
    When "EOF":
            Add "Check for missing closing delimiter" to suggestions
            Add "Verify expression is complete" to suggestions
    Otherwise:
            Add "Check syntax around this token" to suggestions Return suggestions

Note: Grammar Analysis Algorithms
Process called "calculate_first_sets" that takes grammar as Grammar returns Dictionary[String, List[String]]:
    Note: Calculate FIRST sets for all non-terminals
            Let first_sets be dictionary containing
    Let changed be true Note: Initialize FIRST sets
    For each rule_name in keys of grammar.rules:
    Set first_sets at key rule_name to list containing Note: Iterate until no changes
    While changed:
    Set changed to false For each rule_name in keys of grammar.rules:
            Let rule be grammar.rules[rule_name]
    Let old_first_set be first_sets[rule_name] For each production in rule.alternatives:
    Let first_of_production be calculate_first_of_production with production as production and grammar as grammar and first_sets as first_sets For each symbol in first_of_production:
    If not old_first_set contains symbol:
            Add symbol to first_sets[rule_name]
            Set changed to true Return first_sets

Process called "calculate_follow_sets" that takes grammar as Grammar and first_sets as Dictionary[String, List[String]] returns Dictionary[String, List[String]]:
    Note: Calculate FOLLOW sets for all non-terminals
            Let follow_sets be dictionary containing
    Let changed be true Note: Initialize FOLLOW sets
    For each rule_name in keys of grammar.rules:
    Set follow_sets at key rule_name to list containing Note: Add EOF to start rule's FOLLOW set
    Add "EOF" to follow_sets[grammar.start_rule] Note: Iterate until no changes
    While changed:
    Set changed to false For each rule_name in keys of grammar.rules:
    Let rule be grammar.rules[rule_name] For each production in rule.alternatives:
    For i from 0 to (length of production.symbols - 1):
    Let symbol be production.symbols[i] If symbol.symbol_type = NonTerminal:
            Let old_follow_set be follow_sets[symbol.name]
    Let new_symbols be calculate_follow_for_symbol with production as production and position as i and grammar as grammar and first_sets as first_sets and follow_sets as follow_sets For each new_symbol in new_symbols:
    If not old_follow_set contains new_symbol:
