Process called "match_digits" that takes input as String returns Optional[PatternMatch]:
    Note: Match sequence of digits
            Let match_length be 0
    Let input_length be Format.length_of with s as input While match_length < input_length:
            Let char be Format.character_at_index with text as input and index as match_length
    Let char_code be Format.ascii_value_of with char as char If char_code > or equal to 48 and char_code < or equal to 57:
            Set match_length to match_length + 1
    Otherwise:
    Break If match_length > 0:
            Let matched_text be Format.substring with s as input and start as 0 and end as match_length
    Return Some with value as PatternMatch with:
            matched_text as matched_text
            match_length as match_length
            groups as list containing
            metadata as dictionary containing Return None

Process called "match_identifier" that takes input as String returns Optional[PatternMatch]:
    Note: Match identifier pattern [a-zA-Z][a-zA-Z0-9]*
            Let input_length be Format.length_of with s as input
    If input_length = 0:
            Return None Let first_char be Format.character_at_index with text as input and index as 0
    If not is_alpha_char with char as first_char:
    Return None Let match_length be 1 While match_length < input_length:
    Let char be Format.character_at_index with text as input and index as match_length If is_alpha_char with char as char or is_digit_char with char as char:
            Set match_length to match_length + 1
    Otherwise:
            Break Let matched_text be Format.substring with s as input and start as 0 and end as match_length
    Return Some with value as PatternMatch with:
            matched_text as matched_text
            match_length as match_length
            groups as list containing
            metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "is_alpha_char" that takes char as String returns Boolean:
